"top_position": 14,
"top_position_date": "2026-06-30",
"current_position": 19,
"added_at": "2026-06-22T08:15:00.000Z",
"removed_at": null
}
}
}
]
}
}
Deprecations
Historic Engagement Rate Fields
Calculated engagement-rate fields in the /artists/historic_stats, /collaborators/historic_stats, and /labels/historic_stats responses are now deprecated.
This applies to:

• engagement_rate_total for Instagram and TikTok

• video_engagement_rate_total for YouTube videos

• short_engagement_rate_total for YouTube Shorts
{
"source": "instagram",
"data": {
"history": [
{
"date": "2026-07-01",
"views_total": 125400,
"likes_total": 4300,
"comments_total": 210,
"̶e̶n̶g̶a̶g̶e̶m̶e̶n̶t̶_̶r̶a̶t̶e̶_̶t̶o̶t̶a̶l̶"̶:̶ ̶3̶.̶6̶
}
]
}
}
Data Changes
Improved Spotify Stream Count Aggregation
Spotify stream counts are now aggregated using distinct underlying play-count values, preventing duplicate source records from being counted more than once. This provides more accurate Spotify stream totals across tracks, artists, and labels.
We are also refreshing historic Spotify stream counts at the track, artist, and label level so the improved aggregation is reflected consistently throughout the Enterprise API.
